----------------------------------------------------------------------
SCOPE OF THIS PORT
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The Grafana-derived contents of this package are limited to:

  * The time range picker UX shape — composite layout of from/to
    expression fields, presets sidebar, calendar pop, and
    Apply / Cancel controls — re-expressed in egui idiom.

  * The default preset list (labels and semantic intent) shipped
    by Grafana 7.5: "Last 5 minutes" through "This year". Labels
    and semantic intent are Grafana-derived; concrete SQL bodies
    are pebble2impl-authored.

The relative-expression grammar of Grafana's datemath (`now-5m`,
`now/d`, etc.) is NOT ported. Expressions in this package are
ClickHouse SQL fragments evaluated via the `clickhouse-local` CLI;
see ADR-0016 §"Decision".

----------------------------------------------------------------------
MODIFICATIONS APPLIED DURING PORT
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  * Re-implemented from React/TypeScript to Go + Rust. No upstream
    source files were copied verbatim; Grafana's source served as
    a reference for UX shape and preset semantics.

  * Replaced Grafana's datemath grammar with ClickHouse SQL evaluated
    by clickhouse-local. Anchor injected via WITH ... AS anchor_now
    per ADR-0016. The picker is therefore in ClickHouse SQL idiom,
    not Grafana datemath.

  * Translated the default preset list to ClickHouse SQL bodies.
    Labels and semantic intent are Grafana-derived; the SQL bodies
    are pebble2impl-authored.

  * Refactored to the boxer coding standards (see CODINGSTANDARDS.md
    in github.com/stergiotis/boxer): receiver naming convention,
    interface suffix "I", named return values, error builder usage
    (eh.Errorf / eb.Build), sized integer fields on structs,
    compile-time interface assertions.

  * Did not port: Grafana's fiscal-year offset, the auto-refresh
    runner (the picker exposes the interval value; the runner is
    a separate component out of scope for this package), and any
    dashboard-JSON serialisation surface.

Per Apache-2.0 §4.b, files in this package that contain Grafana-
derived material (the presets registry's default labels, primarily)
carry a "Modifications applied during port" line in their header
referencing this NOTICE. Files that are pebble2impl-authored from
scratch (the evaluator subprocess wrapper, the validator, the IDL
definitions, the widget glue) carry no upstream attribution because
they contain no upstream material.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
THIRD-PARTY DEPENDENCIES OF THIS PACKAGE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The aggregate index lives at doc/legal/third_party.md.

This package's only direct in-tree dependency is the ClickHouse SQL
DSL parser at public/db/clickhouse/dsl/, used in-process for
sub-millisecond syntax validation as the user types.

The runtime requirement on the `clickhouse-local` CLI binary is a
process-level dependency, not a build-time link. Tests probe via
exec.LookPath("clickhouse-local") (with `clickhouse local`
fallback) and call t.Skip when the binary is missing; CI does not
install it.

